Detecting Spatial Autocorrelation with MoranI

# extract coordinates matrix
coords = cbind(ppp_bombus$x, ppp_bombus$y)

# calculate distance-based weight matrix
w = fields::rdist(coords)

print("spatial autocorrelation (Moran's I) for variable 'Dist'")
## [1] "spatial autocorrelation (Moran's I) for variable 'Dist'"
ape::Moran.I(ppp_bombus$marks$Dist, w=w)
## $observed
## [1] -0.008786538
## 
## $expected
## [1] -0.001017294
## 
## $sd
## [1] 0.0007187746
## 
## $p.value
## [1] 3.120092e-27
print("spatial autocorrelation (Moran's I) for variable 'DistWater'")
## [1] "spatial autocorrelation (Moran's I) for variable 'DistWater'"
ape::Moran.I(ppp_bombus$marks$DistWater, w=w)
## $observed
## [1] -0.01034395
## 
## $expected
## [1] -0.001017294
## 
## $sd
## [1] 0.0007272121
## 
## $p.value
## [1] 1.184537e-37

Fitting correlation models

Forest

fore_values <- lookup.im(Forest, ppp_bombus$x, ppp_bombus$y)
## Warning in lookup.im(Forest, ppp_bombus$x, ppp_bombus$y): Internal error: NA's
## generated
fore_values[is.na(fore_values)] <- 0
df_fore <- data.frame(Z_s = fore_values, 
                   x = ppp_bombus$x,
                   y = ppp_bombus$y)
ggplot(df_fore, aes(x = x, y = y)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = Z_s, size = Z_s)) +  
  scale_color_gradient(low = "skyblue", high = "yellow") +      
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(1, 3)) +               
  labs(
    title = "Forest Cover at Bombus Locations",
    x = "X-coordinate", 
    y = "Y-coordinate",
    color = "Forest Value", 
    size = "Forest Value"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Variogram for Forest
sp::coordinates(df_fore) <- c("x","y")
vg <- gstat::variogram(Z_s ~ 1, data = df_fore)
plot(vg)

# fit linear model
fit.linear <- gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Lin"))
fit.linear
plot(vg, 
     model = fit.linear,
     main="",
     xlab = "Distance (m)", 
     ylab = "Semi - variance")

# fit spherical model
fit.sph <- gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Sph"))
## Warning in gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Sph")): No convergence
## after 200 iterations: try different initial values?
fit.sph
plot(vg, 
     model = fit.sph,
     main="",
     xlab = "Distance (m)", 
     ylab = "Semi - variance")

# fit Gaussian model
fit.gau <- gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Gau"))
## Warning in gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Gau")): No convergence
## after 200 iterations: try different initial values?
fit.gau
plot(vg, 
     model = fit.gau,
     main="",
     xlab = "Distance (m)", 
     ylab = "Semi - variance")

# fit exp model
fit.exp <- gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Exp"))
fit.exp
plot(vg, 
     model = fit.exp,
     main="",
     xlab = "Distance (m)", 
     ylab = "Semi - variance")

# fit nuggest only model
fit.nug <- gstat::fit.variogram(vg, model = gstat::vgm("Nug"))
fit.nug
plot(vg, 
     model = fit.nug,
     main="",
     xlab = "Distance (m)", 
     ylab = "Semi - variance")

# sse for Forest
results <- data.frame(model = c("spherical", "linear", "Gaussian", "exponential", "nugget"),
                      SSErr = c(attr(fit.sph , "SSErr"),
                                attr(fit.linear , "SSErr"), 
                                attr(fit.gau , "SSErr"), 
                                attr(fit.exp , "SSErr"),
                                attr(fit.nug, "SSErr")))
results <- results[order(results$SSErr),]
results
# compare variance
fit.linear$psill[2] + fit.linear$psill[1]
## [1] 1025.251
var(fore_values)
## [1] 925.8352
# fitted values
fitted <- variogramLine(fit.linear,
                        maxdist = max(vg$dist),
                        dist_vector = vg$dist)

residuals <- fitted$gamma - vg$gamma
plot(residuals - fitted$gamma)
